      "date": "2014-01-07 19:28:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI can't figure out how to leave my replies to Andreas's comments.  They're showing up only as drafts - Perhaps replying here will get them through, but if not:\n---\nAndreas Dilger\n1:15 PM\n\n(improvement) It is better to keep the same author when refreshing someone else's patch, and just add a new Signed-off-by: line.\n---\nAgreed, I didn't realize my doing this would reset that field, it looks like I'll have to manually specify the author when I do the commit.\n\n---\nAndreas Dilger\n1:15 PM\n\n(improvement) I'd have preferred the summary line proposed in the previous inspection (\"mdc: use ibits_known mask for lock match\"), since it makes it clear which mask is being discussed (i.e. the ibits_known mask) and where it is being used (i.e. for lock match).\n\nUnfortunately, it isn't yet possible to edit comments without restarting the whole testing process, but if this patch needs to be refreshed for some other reason I'd appreciate an updated summary line.\n---\nDone.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
